ionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Christiana","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Medieval learned feminine form of   Christian .  As a recent revival it represents an elaborated form of   Christina .  It is also sometimes spelled  <b>Christianna</b> , under the influence of the name   Anna ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Fil","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Aegidus</i>.  See  <b>Gilles</b>    and <b>Giles</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ada","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of uncertain origin; it was not in general use before the late 18th century. It may be a Latinate variant of the biblical name   Adah .  However, it has also been explained as a pet form of   Adele   and   Adelaide  , Germanic female names of which the first element is <i>adal</i> ‘noble’. It was borne by a 7th-century abbess of Saint-Julien-des-Prés at Le Mans."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Christiana Fil Ada de Tarbolton - Lady Graham of Dalkeith was born in 1185, in Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland, her father, Sir Adam FitzGilbert, Knight, was 41 and her mother, Idonea Comyn, was 37. She had at least 1 son with Sir Henry de Graham - Baron of Dalkeith. She died in 1206, in Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 21."},"et":{"1185–1206":"1185–1206","1195–Female":"1195–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1163–1233":"1163–1233","1206–1283":"1206–1283","1144–Male":"1144–Surnud","1148–1232":"1148–1232","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","1144":"1144","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Dalkeith Palace, Midlothian, Scotland":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland","Altyre House, Morayshire, Scotland":"Altyre House, Elginshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1185–1206":"1185–1206","1195–Female":"1195–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1163–1233":"1163–1233","1206–1283":"1206–1283","1144–Male":"1144–Kuollut","1148–1232":"1148–1232","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","1144":"1144","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Dalkeith Palace, Midlothian, Scotland":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland","Altyre House, Morayshire, Scotland":"Altyre House, Elginshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1185–1206":"1185–1206","1195–Female":"1195–Décédée","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1163–1233":"1163–1233","1206–1283":"1206–1283","1144–Male":"1144–Décédé","1148–1232":"1148–1232","1206":"1206","1148":"1148","1233":"1233","1200":"1200","1232":"1232","1144":"1144","1185":"1185","1163":"1163","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","Scotland, United Kingdom":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Tarbolton, Ayrshire, Écosse","Dalkeith Palace, Midlothian, Scotland":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Écosse","Altyre House, Morayshire, Scotland":"Altyre House, Elginshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Lady Christiana Fil Ada de Tarbolton - Lady Graham 